runs.comm: comes round the wicket, drops it short, goes slowly to the batsman and whipped to deep midwicket, protection there
tossed down the leg side, should have swept that away, mistimed to the leg side
tossed up and he comes forward to defend
beaten on the drive and it beats the keeper as well
quicker one and he gets forward to defend
this one skidded though and neatly punched through the gap at cover and point
the first of the match and at Sylhet! Juicy half volley wide outside off and moving away, driven firmly wide of cover
not very convincing though, this was pitched up and he was looking to drive straighter, ended up chipping it over cover and the outfield was quick enough for it to reach the rope
this was hit harder but mistimed, looked to carve it over mid-off but miscued and it lands bear deep cover and doesn't make the rope
he looked to whack this to the on side but played too early, missed and he drags his back foot back

poor shot! Raza looked to repeat the shot from the previous ball, he may have played this too early and the ball came on a bit slower, pulled straight to mid-on where Sorensen hops and takes it over his head
full on the pads and worked to the leg side
full on the pads and worked towards the bowler
beaten on the drive again, skidded through
down the track and he drills it down the ground to long-on
down the leg side and swept fine, short fine leg was in place and Taylor did well to sweep it wide of him
he gets away with this one, down the leg side again but the sweep finds the fielder
punched towards mid-off and they set off quickly, fumble by the fielder but it doesn't cost another run
good length outside the off stump and he chops it straight to backward point
well played! This was drifting down the leg side, short fine leg was in place, Masakadza moved across his stumps and mowed that over the fielder
smashed that down the ground, pitched up outside off and Masakadza gets under the bounce and slams it over mid-off
a bit too straight and he plays it off his pads to the on side
he chops this to the off side for a single
it's a let-off for Masakadza! Pitched up and he looks to loft it over the on side, miscued, it wasmiles in the air and the fielder Cusack back pedals at midwicket and fails to judge it
tossed up and he gets forward to defend
he makes a bit of room and punches it with the turn to cover
gets forward and knocks it to the on side
full on the pads and he works it to the on side
punishes a low full toss, juicy delivery drifting on the pads, Taylor gets on his knee and slams it wide of short fine leg
this was too full and wide outside off, gets across and caresses it wide of mid-off and cover
a bit too straight and he clips it to the on side
the first one in Sylhet! Pitched up on middle, Taylor stays at the crease, bends and slams it over the bowler and down to the sight screen
length ball and no room to free his arms, defends this
tries to run this wide of third man but can't beat the fielder
it  you pitch it up you will get slammed, it was wide outside off and he gets underneath it and scoops it over deep extra cover, it lands just before the rope
gets forward and pushes it to the off side

another wicket off a poor shot! Masakadza went down the track but changed his shot and half heartedly chipped this straight to short midwicket, he was let off earlier but failed to make full use of the chance
almost a third wicket! Tossed up and Williams gets forward and gets a leading edge that lobs over cover
that's more like it, tossed up and Williams gets on his knee and connects the slog sweep very well and clears deep square leg
and that's followed by another leading edge! Ball stopped on him and this time it only just cleared the bowler
he stays back at the crease and knocks it to the on side
quicker one and he pushes it to the off side for a single
tossed up and he clips it to the on side for a single
quicker one and he drives back to the bowler
too full and straight and clipped to the leg side
plays the reverse sweep this time but he ends up placing it straight to short third man, quick single
flatter delivery and he gets well forward and defends
Williams seems to favour the sweep, this was flatter and he was down on his knee early and swept this one wide of deep square leg
flatter one and he stays back and punches this one down to long-off
flatter one and he clips it to the on side

Appeal for a stumping and Williams is walking! And ironically it's the sweep that's cost him his wicket, this was cleverly tossed up McBrine, slowed down the pace and foxed him, Williams was too early on the sweep, he had a long stride forward, Wilson was alert and whipped off the bails immediately, Williams' back foot was outside the crease and he failed to get his bat back on time
on the pads and worked to the on side
flatter one and on the pads and he works it to the on side
drifts down the leg side this time
on the pads and worked to the on side
he stays back and punches it down the ground to long-on
flatter one and he punches it down the ground to long-on
he shuffles and knocks it towards midwicket
tries to squeeze this past midwicket but Porterfield slides and cuts it off
down the track and he doesn't time it properly, chips it towards deep square leg
punches it straight to mid-on
slower through the air and he looks to sweep it from outside off and he fails to connect, rolls off the body
flatter one on the pads and clipped to square leg
works it away past the gap at square leg
tossed up and he drills a low full toss down to long-off
drifts on the body and he works it to the on side
quite effortless! Tossed up and he took a couple of paces down the track and chipped it high over deep midwicket
full on the pads and worked to mid-on
stays back and clips it with the turn to the leg side
he stays back and cuts him straight to point
the bowler runs across to his right and stops a drive
flatter one and he gets forward and defends
he comes forward and punched it to the off side
he comes forward and punches it to cover
gets forward and pushes it with soft hands towards cover and sets off
he gets down to sweep and connects well, it's in the air and on the first bounce to deep square leg, Poynter does well to run to his left and stop it
keeper up to the stumps, he pushes it to the off side
fullish on the stumps and driven down the ground to mid-off
fullish on the stumps and clipped towards midwicket
slower ball on the pads and clipped towards square leg
fullish on the stumps and he pushes it towards mid-off
drops it too short and he is punished, Sibanda read that length early and rocked back and pulled it over midwicket
tossed up and he gets forward and pushes it to the off side and sets off, good running
edged towards short third man and he sets off but is quickly sent back
another one straight to the fielder, this was dropped short and Sibanda couldn't help but go for the pull, rocked back, didn't get the distance, straight to deep midwicket
he stays back and chips it over cover, they push hard for the second
stays back and punches it to the on side
goes back at the crease and punches him down to deep cover
fullish outside off and he drives him down to mid-off
brings up his fifty with a boundary! Slower ball on the stumps and he chips him over midwicket
appeal for an lbw, this skidded through and hit him on the pads, outside the line of leg
that was chipped well, pitched up and he stayed at the crease and lofted it elegantly down the ground
finds the gap again, this was dropped a bit short and he stayed back and pulled it down to deep midwicket, just beat Sorensen at wide long-on
he pushes it to the off side
attempts a reverse sweep and it's a leg bye to the off side
driven to the on side and they think of a single but decide against it
stays back and punches it towards cover
gets down to sweep and can't beat short fine leg

Taylor perishes in the deep and Ireland have picked up an important wicket, tossed up outside off and Taylor went down the track to loft inside out, Joyce jogs to his right at deep extra cover and takes the catch
he gets forward and pushes it to the off side
shuffles across and miscues to to the on side
came on a bit slow and he punched it to the off side
drops it short and he swivels to pull and mistimes it to square leg
flat six! This was dropped short and Maruma read the length early and pulled him over deep square leg, crashes on the boundary board
he makes a bit too much room and ends up chasing it, he forces it to mid-off
pitched up on the pads and Maruma chips this one down to deep midwicket
fuller delivery and he drills this one down to long-on
slower ball and he drills it down to long-on, Maruma wanted a second run
fine leg is up and he gets away with it, he drifts down the leg side and places it to deep square leg
good ball, fuller and he can only drill it wide of cover
this was a low full toss outside off and he chops it down to backward point, only six off the 19th over, good stuff
this was pitched up and chipped down to deep midwicket
breaks the shackles! This was pitched up outside off and he made room and slammed it over deep cover, covered a long distance
this was full and wide and he smashed that down to deep extra cover
fuller and chipped just wide of the bowler and down to long-off
in the slot for Elton! Pitched up and he got under the bounce and slammed that over long-off, the attempted yorker didn't come off
looks to clear long-off again and he mistimes it to the deep, they push for the second but the throw is quick
